WEBVTT

00:02.735 --> 00:06.570
So this is what you wanna do, huh?
You think you want some of me, huh?

00:06.740 --> 00:08.503
Let's go.

00:09.009 --> 00:10.408
Blackjack.

00:12.212 --> 00:13.873
Man, that's three in a row.

00:14.047 --> 00:16.743
I should be taking you to Vegas with me
instead of Carlton.

00:16.916 --> 00:19.714
Yeah, yeah, whatever. Pay the man.

00:27.794 --> 00:28.886
You know what that is?

00:29.062 --> 00:30.859
Irritating.

00:31.331 --> 00:35.768
It's energy generated by the most awesome
source of natural power in the world.

00:35.935 --> 00:38.870
What,
the static from Uncle Phil's corduroys?

00:39.305 --> 00:40.499
The Hoover Dam.

00:40.673 --> 00:45.133
Here, I got you this book so when we get
to Vegas, you'll be Hoover savvy.

00:45.612 --> 00:48.547
I'm getting goose bumps.

00:49.049 --> 00:51.074
You too?

00:51.951 --> 00:53.612
Okay, guys. Here you go.

00:53.787 --> 00:56.483
Here are your airplane tickets
and your hotel confirmation.

00:56.656 --> 00:59.420
Thanks. This is gonna be
the greatest birthday present ever.

00:59.592 --> 01:01.856
It's a shame
you have to go to Sacramento.

01:02.028 --> 01:03.086
Oh, I know. I know.

01:03.263 --> 01:07.222
But, son, this isn't just a birthday,
this is your 21st birthday.

01:07.400 --> 01:11.268
And this isn't just a trip,
it's a rite of passage.

01:11.438 --> 01:14.874
Cheyenne Indians used to take
a young brave and leave him in the desert...

01:15.041 --> 01:17.908
...and he'd have to fend for himself
with nothing but a knife.

01:18.078 --> 01:20.911
But when he left that desert,
he was a man.

01:22.816 --> 01:26.684
There's certainly some places in this desert
where a brother can become a man.

01:28.455 --> 01:31.185
I don't know where none of them at,
you know, you know, but...

01:31.357 --> 01:33.291
I'm gonna go ahead and get my knife.

