02:58.278 --> 02:59.677
Aww.

02:59.846 --> 03:02.314
Okay, ladies, I'm leaving.

03:04.517 --> 03:07.384
They don't hear you, sir.
They've begun their women's weekend.

03:07.554 --> 03:12.423
Right now, they're in phase one.
Chick flicks and mint Milanos.

03:14.961 --> 03:17.327
I said, I'm leaving.

03:24.437 --> 03:28.134
Well, it's not like
you're going off to war, sir.

03:30.777 --> 03:35.840
I just know that one day Thelma and Louise
will make it to the other side of the canyon.

03:49.529 --> 03:51.258
Somebody pinch me.

03:51.431 --> 03:55.561
I'm in the same city with Tom Jones,
Wayne Newton, and Engelbert Humperdinck.

03:56.636 --> 04:01.596
So many shows, so little time. Ugh.

04:08.248 --> 04:14.209
I can't believe I'm in the same city
as Girls, Girls, Girls. Oh!

04:14.387 --> 04:17.048
So many shows, so little time.

04:19.759 --> 04:21.192
Whoo-hoo!

04:21.361 --> 04:23.420
Bells ringing, money flowing.

04:23.596 --> 04:26.156
We are certainly not in Kansas anymore.

04:28.534 --> 04:34.063
Oh, Auntie Em, Dorothy got a miniskirt on.

04:34.707 --> 04:39.041
We've entered the world of temptation.
A word to the wise, beware.

04:39.212 --> 04:42.841
All right, here's the plan.
First, we split up...

04:43.016 --> 04:45.041
- And?
- That's it. We just split up.

04:45.218 --> 04:46.242
All right, I get it.

04:46.419 --> 04:49.650
We'll gamble for about an hour or so,
but then we have to hit the hay.

04:49.822 --> 04:52.052
We don't wanna miss sunrise
at Hoover Dam.

04:52.225 --> 04:55.251
They say it starts out mauve.

04:56.095 --> 04:58.928
You're an odd little man, aren't you?

04:59.432 --> 05:00.456
Yeah.

05:11.244 --> 05:12.541
Change for a dollar, please.

05:13.346 --> 05:15.439
There's a $5 minimum, sir.

05:15.615 --> 05:17.981
Outrageous. We're out of here, Will.

05:18.151 --> 05:20.346
Whoa, wait a minute, Carlton.
Relax, man.

05:20.520 --> 05:22.147
Can I get change for 100, please?

05:22.322 --> 05:25.314
